<subSubSection id="C3246572FF96C939FF62FEC1FD1AFE4A" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B8136F9FF96C939FF62FEC1FD1AFE4A" blockId="55.[151,1437,259,502]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF96C939FF62FEC1FEC0FEA6" bold="true" box="[199,334,331,357]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name refers to the Indigenous tribe 
<taxonomicName id="4C3E4D7AFF96C939FC33FEC1FC54FEA6" box="[918,986,331,357]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" rank="tribe" tribe="Paiaia">Paiaia</taxonomicName>
that originally inhabited the region of Miguel Calmon in 
<collectingRegion id="49FAF81BFF96C939FEC9FEE5FE3FFE4A" box="[364,433,367,393]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Bahia</collectingRegion>
; noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3246572FF96C939FF62FE19FCB3FE36" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B8136F9FF96C939FF62FE19FCB3FE36" blockId="55.[151,1437,259,502]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF96C939FF62FE19FECCFE6E" bold="true" box="[199,322,403,429]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Females of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3E4D7AFF96C939FE6BFE1EFDB3FE6E" authority="Rheims &amp; Jäger, 2022" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Jäger" authorityYear="2022" box="[462,573,404,429]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Meri" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paiaia" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF96C939FE6BFE1EFDB3FE6E" box="[462,573,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">M. paiaia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF96C939FDE1FE19FD11FE6E" bold="true" box="[580,671,403,429]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2795790FF96C939FDE1FE19FD11FE6E" box="[580,671,403,429]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
are distinguished from those of the other congeners by the epigyne with MS resembling an upside-down brandy glass (
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFF96C939FD78FE3DFCB0FE12" box="[733,830,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURES 208–216" captionStartId="54.[151,264,1743,1767]" captionTargetBox="[155,1418,195,1708]" captionTargetId="figure-23@54.[155,1432,181,1720]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="FIGURES 208–216. 208–210 Meri mathani (Simon) comb. nov., female (MNHN 2028, lectotype) (208 epigyne, 209 vulva, 210 schematic course of internal duct system); 211–213 Meri munduruku spec. nov., female (MPEG 30776, holotype) (211 epigyne, 212 vulva 213 schematic course of internal duct system); 214–216 Meri paiaia spec. nov., female (IBSP 167988, holotype) (214 epigyne, 215 vulva, 216 schematic course of internal duct system). EP—epigynal pocket; FD—fertilization duct; ft—first turn of duct system; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; MS—median septum; SP—spermathecae. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550344" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550344/files/figure.png" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Fig. 214</figureCitation>
) and the internal ducts with first turn and GP anterior to copulatory openings (
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFF96C939FE02FE51FDC8FE35" box="[423,582,475,502]" captionStart="FIGURES 208–216" captionStartId="54.[151,264,1743,1767]" captionTargetBox="[155,1418,195,1708]" captionTargetId="figure-23@54.[155,1432,181,1720]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="FIGURES 208–216. 208–210 Meri mathani (Simon) comb. nov., female (MNHN 2028, lectotype) (208 epigyne, 209 vulva, 210 schematic course of internal duct system); 211–213 Meri munduruku spec. nov., female (MPEG 30776, holotype) (211 epigyne, 212 vulva 213 schematic course of internal duct system); 214–216 Meri paiaia spec. nov., female (IBSP 167988, holotype) (214 epigyne, 215 vulva, 216 schematic course of internal duct system). EP—epigynal pocket; FD—fertilization duct; ft—first turn of duct system; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; MS—median septum; SP—spermathecae. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550344" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550344/files/figure.png" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Figs 215–216</figureCitation>
). Males are unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF416671FF96C939FF32F89AFB42F88F" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550346" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6550346" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550346/files/figure.png" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" startId="55.[151,264,1808,1832]" targetBox="[171,1404,529,1763]" targetPageId="55">
<paragraph id="8B8136F9FF96C939FF32F89AFB42F88F" blockId="55.[151,1436,1808,1869]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF96C939FF32F89AFEE0F8EB" bold="true" box="[151,366,1808,1832]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">FIGURES 217–220.</emphasis>
217–218 
<taxonomicName id="4C3E4D7AFF96C939FE73F89BFD0CF8EA" authority="Rheims &amp; Jäger, 2022" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Jäger" authorityYear="2022" box="[470,642,1809,1833]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Meri" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="munduruku" status="spec. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF96C939FE73F89BFD0CF8EA" box="[470,642,1809,1833]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Meri munduruku</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF96C939FD2FF89BFD7CF8EA" bold="true" box="[650,754,1809,1833]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2795790FF96C939FD2FF89BFD7CF8EA" box="[650,754,1809,1833]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" rank="species">spec. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, female (MPEG 30776, holotype) (217 epigyne, 218 vulva); 219– 220 
<taxonomicName id="4C3E4D7AFF96C939FF61F8BFFEB2F88F" authority="Rheims &amp; Jäger, 2022" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Jäger" authorityYear="2022" box="[196,316,1845,1868]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Meri" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paiaia" status="spec. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF96C939FF61F8BFFEB2F88F" box="[196,316,1845,1868]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Meri paiaia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF96C939FEE7F8BFFE27F88E" bold="true" box="[322,425,1845,1869]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2795790FF96C939FEE7F8BFFE27F88E" box="[322,425,1845,1869]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" rank="species">spec. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, female (IBSP 167988, holotype) (219 epigyne, 220 vulva). Scale lines: 1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="C3246572FF96C936FF62F8F1FE0AFEA6" lastPageId="56" lastPageNumber="57" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B8136F9FF96C936FF62F8F1FE58FE82" blockId="55.[151,1437,1914,2014]" lastBlockId="56.[151,1437,151,393]" lastPageId="56" lastPageNumber="57" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF96C939FF62F8F1FDCDF857" bold="true" box="[199,579,1914,1941]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
Description. Female (
<typeStatus id="5485885BFF96C939FE6DF8F0FDB8F857" box="[456,566,1914,1940]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">holotype</typeStatus>
):
</emphasis>
